* Idea layer (Garden / White Light) → infinite possibilities
* Embodiment layer (Sieve / Constraint / Arena) → only what works persists
* Memory layer (Money Bin / Invariants) → what survives gets stored

That’s why embodiment feels like “what’s missing”—
because it’s the filter that decides what’s real vs. just elegant.

